  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which is the best haircut for man?",
  "response": "The \"best\" haircut for a man depends on various factors, including face shape, hair type, lifestyle, and personal style preferences. Here are some popular and versatile haircuts that work well for many men:\n\n### 1. **Classic Taper Cut**\n   - **Description:** Short and clean with the sides and back gradually tapered.\n   - **Best For:** All face shapes, especially square or oval.\n   - **Why It Works:** Low maintenance, professional, and timeless.\n\n### 2. **Crew Cut**\n   - **Description:** Very short on the sides and back, slightly longer on top.\n   - **Best For:** Oval, round, or athletic builds.\n   - **Why It Works:** Simple, masculine, and easy to maintain.\n\n### 3. **Textured Crop**\n   - **Description:** Short with textured layers on top for a messy, modern look.\n   - **Best For:** Square, oval, or heart-shaped faces.\n   - **Why It Works:** Trendy, versatile, and works with thick or thin hair.\n\n### 4. **Undercut**\n   - **Description:** Shaved or closely cropped sides with longer hair on top.\n   - **Best For:** Square, oval, or diamond-shaped faces.\n   - **Why It Works:** Edgy, stylish, and allows for creative styling on top.\n\n### 5. **Side Part**\n   - **Description:** Classic comb-over with a defined side part.\n   - **Best For:** Oval, square, or rectangular faces.\n   - **Why It Works:** Polished, professional, and great for formal or casual settings.\n\n### 6. **Pompadour**\n   - **Description:** Short sides with voluminous, swept-back hair on top.\n   - **Best For:** Oval, square, or heart-shaped faces.\n   - **Why It Works:** Bold, retro, and perfect for making a statement.\n\n### 7. **Fade (Low, Mid, or High)**\n   - **Description:** Gradual transition from short to even shorter hair on the sides and back.\n   - **Best For:** All face shapes and hair types.\n   - **Why It Works:** Clean, modern, and highly customizable.\n\n### 8. **French Crop**\n   - **Description:** Short on the sides with a cropped, textured fringe.\n   - **Best For:** Oval, square, or round faces.\n   - **Why It Works:** Minimalist, stylish, and easy to manage.\n\n### 9. **Long Layers**\n   - **Description:** Shoulder-length or longer hair with layers for movement and texture.\n   - **Best For:** Oval, heart, or rectangular faces.\n   - **Why It Works:** Masculine, flowing, and great for a relaxed or bohemian vibe.\n\n### 10. **Buzz Cut**\n   - **Description:** Uniformly short all over.\n   - **Best For:** Oval or square faces with strong features.\n   - **Why It Works:** Ultra-low maintenance, bold, and timeless.\n\n### Tips for Choosing the Right Haircut:\n- **Face Shape:** Identify your face shape (oval, round, square, heart, etc.) to find a style that complements your features.\n- **Hair Type:** Consider your hair texture (straight, wavy, curly, or thinning) to ensure the haircut works for you.\n- **Lifestyle:** Choose a style that fits your daily routine and maintenance preferences.\n- **Consult a Barber:** A professional can recommend the best haircut based on your unique features and hair type.\n\nUltimately, the best haircut is one that makes you feel confident and suits your personal style!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
